impression: IMPRESSION: Goitrous thyroid with diffuse uneven echogenicity.
Small smooth solitary smooth nodules bilaterally as described.
These are below the criteria for biopsy but can be done if there
is strong clinical suspicion for malignancy.
Electronically signed by Eric Tao on 3/4/2016 4:15 PM
narrative: HISTORY: Thyromegaly and multinodular thyroid
COMPARISON: None
FINDINGS: Both the left and right lobes are within upper limits
of normal in size.
The right lobe measures 4.9 x 2.0 x 1.2 cm. Diffuse inhomogeneous
echogenicity is seen throughout the right lobe. There is a smooth
well defined isoechoic oval solid nodule without calcifications
located at the upper right lobe. It measures 1.1 x 0.8 x 0.6 cm.
Slight diffuse increase in vascularity is seen with Doppler.
The left lobe measures 4.6 x 2.0 x 1.4 cm. Similar diffuse
inhomogeneous echogenicity is also seen throughout the left lobe.
There is a similar smooth oval isoechoic solid nodule without
calcifications at the mid left lobe. This nodule measures 1.3 x
1.1 x 0.9 cm. Similar slight diffuse increase in vascularity is
seen with Doppler.
Isthmus thickness is normal at 2 mm. Incidental finding of small
nodules inferior to the thyroid measuring well less than 1 cm.
These are probably nonspecific lymph nodes.
